KW  - Price indices
KW  - Production theory
KW  - Input deflation
AB  - This paper extends work by Fisher and Shell (1972) on the production-theoretic treatment of output deflation to the case of input deflation (see also Muellbauer, 1972). Input deflation is examined for a multi-product firm (or sector) in three cases: 1.(a) selling at fixed prices,2.(b) with monopoly power over some outputs,3.(c) operating as a perfectly competitive industry but facing downward-sloping demand curves. The latter case is particularly complex, and Paasche and Laspeyres bounds are show not to apply. Issues such as the treatment of quality change (hedonics) are also examined.
